The cruise allows visitors to enjoy the splendor of the historic town of Grand Bay and sail towards Coin de Mire with its spectacular sea cliffs, offering breathtaking views of other northern islands and Mauritius''s central mountain range. 

The catamaran features spacious outdoor areas on the deck, front, and back, specially designed for sunset viewing, photography, and socializing. It includes a bar, high-end audio system, and refined music collection.', 'Catamaran cruises', 'North - Grand Baie', '120', 'Grand Baie', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Cocktail Cruise: Canapés (tuna, shrimp, smoked fish)","Peanuts, chips","Wine Cocktails (white, rosé)","Beer, Rum","Non-alcoholic drinks","Mineral water","Dinner Cruise: Selection of canapés and snacks","Baby seat available free on request"}'::text[], '{"Transportation to/from boarding point (available separately)","Please, do not drink if you are going to drive!","Arrive at boarding point at least 15 minutes before cruise start time"}'::text[], '{"Grand Baie (Northern Region)","Gunner''s Coin / Coin de Mire (Northern Region) - spectacular cliffs with an explosion of color","Sunset viewing over the northwest coast","Sail past Fort Malarctic and Cap Malheureux"}'::text[], 'Full Refund up to 24 hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'North', NULL, NULL, '3', 'f', 'f', '0');

The adventure starts with a visit to the famous Grand River South East Waterfall, followed by a scenic cruise past lush forests, where you may spot monkeys, bats, and the iconic white-tailed tropicbird. 

Continue exploring the beautiful offshore islands, including Flamingo Island, the historic Lighthouse Island (Île aux Fouquets), and Île de la Passe. Enjoy time to snorkel in the crystal-clear waters near Île aux Aigrettes and the renowned Eau Bleue, home to vibrant tropical marine life. 

Around midday, relax on board as you indulge in a delicious BBQ lunch featuring fresh salads, grilled chicken, fish, sausages, and dessert while anchored in calm waters. 

After lunch, spend free time on the world-famous Île aux Cerfs, where you can swim, relax on the white sandy beaches, or simply soak up the tropical paradise before cruising back to Trou d''Eau Douce in the afternoon with unforgettable memories of your day at sea.', 'Private Cruises', 'Trou D''eau Douce', '480', 'Route Royale Maho, Trou d''Eau Douce', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{Lunch,Drinks,"Visit ile aux cerfs","Visit GRSE waterfalls","Visit lighthouse island (ile aux fouquets)","Snorkeling gear available","Professional Crew","Vegetarian/gluten free meals available on request"}'::text[], '{"Pick-Up/Drop-off at additional cost","Water Activities not included(e.g: parasailing etc...)"}'::text[], '{"Grande Rivière Sud-Est (GRSE) waterfall","Snorkeling among coral gardens and tropical fish at Eau Bleue","Île aux Aigrettes (Southeast Region)","Île aux Prison (Southeast Region)","Île Phare / Île aux Phare (Southeast Region)","Beaches of northern Île aux Cerfs and the turquoise lagoon","BBQ lunch on board"}'::text[], 'Free cancellation up to 24 hours before your activity for a full refund.', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-07-08 17:23:58.153099+00', '{"isPrivate": true, "itinerary": [{"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Route Royale Maho, Trou d''Eau Douce", "description": "Departure"}, {"area": null, "tags": ["Sightseeing", "Pass By", "Scenic view"], "title": "Grand River South East", "description": null}, {"area": null, "tags": ["Sightseeing", "Snorkeling", "Swimming", "Marine life viewing"], "title": "Fouquets Island", "description": "Secret spot"}, {"area": null, "tags": ["Sightseeing"], "title": "Île de la Passe", "description": null}, {"area": null, "tags": ["Break time", "Photo stop", "Drink", "Swimming"], "title": "Aigrette Island", "description": null}, {"area": null, "tags": ["Photo Stop", "Visit", "Boat Cruise", "Walk", "Swimming", "Scenic view on the way"], "title": "Île aux Cerfs", "description": null}], "startWindow": "09:00"}'::jsonb, '20', 'per_group', 'f', 'East', NULL, NULL, '2', 'f', 'f', '1');

The minimum rental duration is 6 hours, and a boat can be shared by a maximum of three anglers. The boats operate from the north, west, and east coasts. You will sail along the reef and observe the corals up close, explore the rich local marine life.', 'Sea & water activities', 'West', '480', 'Black River', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Experienced skipper guidance","Modern, well-equipped boats","Access to three departure locations (north, west, east coasts)","Drinks included (Beer, soft drinks & water)"}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '{"Fish for Blue Marlin, Dorado and other large fish","Sail along the reef and observe corals up close","Explore local marine life"}'::text[], 'Cancel before 24hours for a full refund', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_group', 'f', 'West', NULL, NULL, '3', 'f', 'f', '0');

On the West coast of Mauritius, we offer a large selection of trips, both on a shared basis and private basis. All the activities are done under the instructions and supervision of professional skippers and crew members while respecting and protecting the aquatic life and natural environment. The first part of this excursion will give you the opportunity to admire the biggest and largest marine animal. Either the humpback whales or the sperm whales these cetaceans remain wild and unpredictable, so it is not 100% guaranteed to meet them, just like dolphins but our dedicated crew members most of time do their best to make our guests enjoy an unforgettable and a lifetime memory.

 After this pure moment of happiness, it will be time to search for the joyful, playful, intelligent and charming Dolphins. A briefing about the rules to respect concerning the approach, as well as all safety measures will be given by the boat captain or crew members before getting into the water. 

Then you will enjoy the magical snorkeling moment with one of the most fantastic creatures under the supervision of an instructor. While cruising back depending on the time remaining, the boat trip may continue at the Aquarium, a magical snorkeling site to discover and enjoy the Mauritian aquatic life. Then the boat will be heading back to the shore where your journey will end happily thinking of your most recent encounter.', 'Speedboat Tours', 'Tamarin', '240', 'Tamarin', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Professional skipper and crew supervision","Complimentary refreshments (water and soft drinks)"}'::text[], '{"Children under 12 must be accompanied by an adult"}'::text[], '{"Admire humpback or sperm whales","Return to shore","Swim with spinner and bottlenose dolphins in their natural environment"}'::text[], 'Full refund up to 24 hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{}'::jsonb, NULL, 'per_person', 'f', 'West', NULL, NULL, '3', 'f', 'f', '0');

Tropical fauna and flora await discovery both in the water and on the island. After a BBQ lunch, the boat proceeds to Gabriel Island for exploration. A final snorkeling session takes place near Gunner''s Coin, one of the most beautiful diving spots off the north of Mauritius.', 'Speedboat Tours', 'Grand Bay', '420', 'Grand Bay', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Salads and garlic butter bread","BBQ: chicken, fish, sausage","Beverages: water, Coke, beer, wine, local rum","Dessert: flaming banana","Snorkeling sessions","Pick-up and drop-off available across the island"}'::text[], '{"Do not drink if you are going to drive","Arrive at least 15 minutes before the cruise start time"}'::text[], '{"Flat Island: relaxation, snorkeling and BBQ lunch","Gabriel Island: island exploration","Gunner''s Coin: snorkeling at one of the most beautiful diving spots off the north of Mauritius"}'::text[], 'Full refund up to 24 hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'North', NULL, NULL, '3', 'f', 'f', '0');

THE MAGIC (departing from Triolet, North): Discover beautiful panoramas of Mauritius by flying over the island for 40 minutes with our exclusive Le Magique experience. The adventure begins with a majestic take-off from our base in Triolet, where our dedicated team gives you the warmest of welcomes. Enjoy a moment of relaxation in our elegant lounge, followed by a complete flight briefing for an unforgettable experience. Then embark on a fascinating aerial excursion that will reveal the hidden treasures of Mauritius. Admire the breathtaking view of Port-Louis, fly over the iconic silos of the Moulin de la Concorde, watch the ships filling the capital, marvel at the vast green spaces and crystal-clear lagoon, discover Ile aux Benitiers and contemplate the majestic Albion lighthouse that proudly dominates its surroundings. An unforgettable experience awaits you, ready to transform your vision of Mauritius forever. If you are wondering which is that majestic mountain where the tropicbirds live, it is the Morne Brabant! Do not miss the Underwater Waterfall and admire the magnificent colours of Chamarel. Relax on the white sand beaches of Ile aux Cerfs and enjoy the tropical sun while sipping a refreshing cocktail. Explore the Riviere-Noire gorges to discover the beauty of raw nature, then admire the Tamarin waterfalls hidden in an endemic forest. Dive into the crystal-clear waters of Blue Bay Marine Park for an unforgettable diving experience among the corals and colourful fish. Approach Le Pieter Both, a mountain linked to a famous legend, before ending your journey with a breathtaking flyover with Corail Helicopteres! Do not forget to taste the delights of local Mauritian cuisine, such as chicken curry and spicy samosas, for an authentic culinary experience.

THE EXCELLENCE (departing from Triolet, North): You will circle around Pieter Both and Le Pouce to get your adventure off to a great start. Then admire the beautiful panorama of the Tamarin Waterfall in the middle of a verdant forest and rocks sculpted by Mother Nature. You will also feel as if you are flying with the tropicbirds as you approach the Riviere-Noire Gorges. After a detour to Ile aux Benitiers, capture the Underwater Waterfall near Morne Brabant, listed as a UNESCO heritage site. You may wonder whether the rainbow has fallen when you fly over Chamarel. The magic is always present here! Have you ever seen an islet in the middle of a lake? Live this unique experience at Ganga Talao. Do not forget to take a look at the crater of the sleeping Kanaka volcano in Mauritius. As you approach the island, fly over Ile aux Cerfs in the east, then head back north passing over Ile d''Ambre and Ile Plate, famous for its artistically patterned chameleons! Near Cap Malheureux lies Le Coin de Mire, visible from our base if the clouds allow! This is Mauritius in all its splendour!', 'Air activities', 'Triolet base (North), Mauritius. Belle Mare Tours Ltd, Royal Road, Belle Mare, Mauritius. Directions to the boarding point are available on Google Maps.', '25', NULL, 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Scenic aerial flight (itinerary depending on the package)","Complete flight briefing (The Magic)","Access to the elegant lounge (The Magic)"}'::text[], '{"Transport is optional (do not drink if you are going to drive)"}'::text[], '{"The Must: flyover of the northern landscapes and islets, Grand-Baie, Coin de Mire, Ile Plate, Ile d''Ambre (site of the Saint-Geran shipwreck)","The Magic: Port-Louis, Moulin de la Concorde, Ile aux Benitiers, Morne Brabant, the Underwater Waterfall, Chamarel, Ile aux Cerfs, Riviere-Noire, the Tamarin waterfalls, Blue Bay Marine Park, Pieter Both","The Excellence: Pieter Both, Le Pouce, Tamarin Waterfall, Riviere-Noire Gorges, Ile aux Benitiers, the Underwater Waterfall, Morne Brabant, Chamarel, Ganga Talao, the Kanaka volcano crater, Ile aux Cerfs, Ile d''Ambre, Ile Plate, Cap Malheureux, Coin de Mire"}'::text[], NULL, 'draft'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{}'::jsonb, NULL, 'per_person', 'f', 'North', NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '0');

You can find a wide variety of plants and exotic birds in this peaceful and enchanting location. It is recommended to be accompanied by a guide who will assist you during the hike as there are not many precise trails to follow.', 'Hiking & Land Adventures', 'Centre', NULL, 'Henrietta', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Professional Guide","Water included"}'::text[], '{"Bring water","Comfortable hiking shoes","Sunscreen and mosquito repellent","In case you want to go swimming, bring your swimsuits and towels too"}'::text[], '{"Tamarind Falls (7 Cascades), the highest waterfall in Mauritius at 293 meters / 961 feet","Wide variety of plants and exotic birds","Peaceful and enchanting location on the high plateaus","Optional swimming"}'::text[], 'Full Refund up to 24 hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{"startWindow": "08:00 - 12:00"}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'West', NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '0');

Reach out and touch the clouds while marveling at the magnificence of the turquoise lagoons and lush mountain ranges that stretch out before you as you effortlessly gaze towards the horizon. 

Explore the tumultuous history, folklore, and myths that have surrounded the mountain and celebrate the triumph of reaching the summit after bravely tackling the thrilling climbing terrains you will encounter. 

Designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2006, the mountain is a protected sanctuary for the plethora of rare plant and animal species that continue to thrive.', 'Hiking & Land Adventures', 'South West', '210', 'Le Morne Brabant', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Guided Hike on the Le Morne Slave Route","Water provided","Local Mountain Guides(Licensed by Mauritius Tourism Authority)"}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '{"Climb from base to the peak of the ''V'' summit","Spectacular views of turquoise lagoons and lush mountain ranges","Explore the mountain''s history, folklore, and myths","UNESCO World Heritage Site, sanctuary for rare plant and animal species","Distance: 5.6 km; elevation gain: 465 m"}'::text[], 'Full Refund up to 24 hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{"adultsOnly": true, "startWindow": "06:00"}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'South', NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '0');

Accompanied by knowledgeable guides, you''ll enjoy breathtaking coastal scenery, refreshing sea breezes, and the peaceful charm of Mauritius'' pristine beaches. Ideal for couples, families, and solo travelers alike, this unique horseback adventure offers an unforgettable way to experience the island''s natural beauty.

Please note that this ride is at a walk along the beach only. For a different type of ride, including trotting, galloping, and swimming with the horses, please contact us directly. Optional photoshoot available; please contact us for a customized tour.', 'Hiking & Land Adventures', 'Belle Mare Beach', '60', 'Belle Mare Beach', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Helmet rental","1-hour horseback ride on Belle Mare Beach","Experienced guide to accompany you"}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '{"Trained horses in good condition","Friendly team at your service","Rider weight limit set at 200 lbs."}'::text[], 'Free cancellation up to 24 hours before your activity for a full refund.', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-07-07 15:41:59.940672+00', '{"startWindow": "09:00"}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'East', NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '1');

An exhibition room and fern garden showcase native flowers such as Trochetia and Banané Bouquet. Wildlife includes tortoises, monkeys, deer, fish and birds such as the Pink Pigeon and the Paille-en-Queue. 

Endemic trees (Ebony, Rattan Wood, Takamaka) enhance the scenery. Four waterfalls — Vacoas, Rattan Wood, Angel Hair and Chamouzé — offer relaxation spots. The main attraction is the earth with 23 distinct colours, originating from the Bassin Blanc volcano eruption millions of years ago.', 'Hiking & Land Adventures', 'Chamouny, South Region', '420', 'Chamouny', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Entrance Fee","Visit to the Park"}'::text[], '{Lunch,"Guide services"}'::text[], '{"23-coloured earth formation","Four waterfalls (Vacoas, Rattan Wood, Angel Hair, Chamouzé)","Exhibition room","Fern garden with native flowers","Wildlife viewing (tortoises, monkeys, deer, birds)","Endemic tree species (Ebony, Rattan Wood, Takamaka)","South Coast panoramic views"}'::text[], 'Full Refund up to 24 Hours', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-06-19 20:14:04.421184+00', '{"priceList": {"url": "https://dwjkfowhrrvdiqligxcj.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/activity-images/la-vallee-des-couleurs-nature-park-2/pricelist-1783247264197-m4vzgj.pdf", "label": "Vallee Price List"}, "startWindow": "09:00 - 17:00"}'::jsonb, '10', 'per_person', 'f', 'South', NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '0');

Your journey begins in Port Louis, the vibrant capital city, where you can visit the Central Market, Caudan Waterfront, and Chinatown. Continue to the historic Citadel Fortress for breathtaking panoramic views of the city and harbour.

Next, visit the famous Pamplemousses Botanical Garden, one of the oldest botanical gardens in the Southern Hemisphere, known for its giant water lilies and exotic plants. Continue to Château de Labourdonnais, a beautifully restored colonial mansion surrounded by lush orchards.

Head north to the picturesque village of Cap Malheureux and admire its iconic red-roof church overlooking the turquoise lagoon. Along the way, enjoy scenic coastal views, local culture, and opportunities to take memorable photos.

This private tour offers flexibility, comfort, and personalized service, making it perfect for couples, families, and small groups seeking to experience the best of North Mauritius in one unforgettable day.', 'Taxi Sightseeing tours', 'North', '480', 'Hotel, Airbnb, guesthouse or cruise-port pickup across Mauritius', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Private transportation in a comfortable air-conditioned vehicle","Professional driver-guide","Hotel, Airbnb, or port pickup and drop-off","Flexible itinerary and photo stops","Fuel and parking fees"}'::text[], '{"Entrance fees to attractions and museums","Personal expenses and souvenirs","Optional activities not mentioned in the itinerary","Food and beverages not included. (Driver will recommend where to eat)"}'::text[], '{"Explore Port Louis and its bustling central market","Grand Baie and the iconic red-roof church of Cap Malheureux","A private driver-guide at your service all day","Fully customisable itinerary — add turtles, diving or Château de Labourdonnais","Pamplemousses Botanical Garden — giant water lilies and exotic plants(Rs300 entrance fee per person)"}'::text[], 'Free cancellation up to 24 hours before for a full refund.', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, '4.8', '126', '2026-06-14 22:39:52.369676+00', '{"itinerary": [{"area": "Capital", "tags": ["Guided tour", "Sightseeing", "Photo stop"], "title": "Port Louis", "description": null}, {"area": "Capital", "tags": ["Visit", "Shopping", "Walk"], "title": "Central Market", "description": null}, {"area": "North", "tags": ["Visit", "Guided tour", "Walk"], "title": "Pamplemousses Botanical Garden", "description": null}, {"area": "North", "tags": ["Free time", "Photo stop"], "title": "Grand Baie", "description": null}, {"area": "North", "tags": ["Photo stop", "Sightseeing"], "title": "Cap Malheureux", "description": null}]}'::jsonb, '10', 'vehicle', 'f', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 'f', 'f', '0');

Your journey begins with a visit to the majestic Grande Rivière Sud-Est Waterfall, one of Mauritius'' most spectacular natural attractions. Continue with a snorkeling stop among vibrant coral gardens, where you can swim alongside colorful tropical fish in crystal-clear waters.

Cruise to the picturesque offshore islands, including Île aux Aigrettes, Île aux Prison, and Île au Phare, each offering unique scenery, fascinating history, and unspoiled natural beauty.

Enjoy a delicious BBQ lunch in a tranquil setting on the southern side of Île aux Cerfs before spending the afternoon relaxing on the island''s beautiful northern beaches. Swim in the turquoise lagoon, soak up the tropical atmosphere, or simply unwind at your own pace before returning to Trou d''Eau Douce.', 'Private Cruises', 'East', '420', 'Route Royale Maho, Trou d''Eau Douce', 't', '{English,French}'::text[], '{"Lunch and drinks","BBQ lunch with salads, garlic butter bread, chicken, fish, sausage","Drinks: water, Coke, beer, wine, local rum","Flaming banana dessert","Snorkeling session","Visit to five islands",Pickup(optional)}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '{"Grande Rivière Sud-Est (GRSE) waterfall","Snorkeling among coral gardens and tropical fish at Eau Bleue","Île aux Aigrettes (Southeast Region)","Île aux Prison (Southeast Region)","Île Phare / Île aux Phare (Southeast Region)","BBQ lunch on the southern part of Île aux Cerfs","Beaches of northern Île aux Cerfs and the turquoise lagoon"}'::text[], 'Free cancellation up to 24 hours before your activity for a full refund.', 'published'::activity_status, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2026-07-13 17:47:51.344047+00', '{"itinerary": [{"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Trou d''eau douce", "description": "Departure"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Ile aux cerfs", "description": "Visit Sightseeing"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Ile aux cerf Island", "description": "Lunch Bbq and drinks on the beach"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "G.R.S.E Waterfall", "description": "Visit Sightseeing"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Ile aux phare", "description": "Visit Sightseeing"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Ile de passe", "description": "Photos"}, {"area": null, "tags": [], "title": "Aigrette island", "description": "Swimming,Snorkeling"}], "startWindow": "09:00", "whatToBring": ["Sunglasses", "Hat", "Swimwear", "Towel", "Snorkeling gear"], "importantInfo": ["You will visit 3 islands, subject to tid